\title{Varjo Xr 4}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Varjo XR-4 Series device profile for reality tech. Covers Varjo Base, OpenXR/OpenVR runtime setup, tracking options (inside-out vs SteamVR), and wide-gamut display notes.}

\subtree{
\title{Varjo XR-4 Series (Device Profile)}
\p{Use when the user targets Varjo XR-4 / XR-4 Focal Edition / XR-4 Secure Edition.}

\subtree{
\title{What Matters Most}
\ul{
\li{Wide-gamut mini-LED displays (98\% sRGB / 96\% DCI-P3) and high PPD (up to 51)}
\li{Windows + Varjo Base is the control plane}
\li{OpenXR is the default modern API target; OpenVR is still relevant for SteamVR apps}
\li{Tracking mode choice changes your deployment: inside-out vs base-station (SteamVR)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Setup + Runtime}
\ul{
\li{Install Varjo Base.}
\li{If prompted, enable OpenXR and OpenVR runtimes (needed for OpenXR apps and SteamVR/OpenVR apps).}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Tracking Options}
\ul{
\li{Inside-out tracking (no base stations)}
\li{SteamVR Tracking on base station tracking variants (base stations + optional controllers/trackers)}
\li{Third-party tracking (ART/OptiTrack) via API integrations}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Refresh Rate (Practical)}
\ul{
\li{Typical options are 75 Hz or 90 Hz (configured in Varjo Base).}
\li{90 Hz is the safer default for VR comfort if you can hit frame rate; 75 Hz can reduce GPU load.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Color / Rendering Notes}
\ul{
\li{XR-4 has high DCI-P3 coverage; for color-critical work, validate your look in-headset.}
\li{Treat wide-gamut as a display capability, not a guarantee of correct color: calibration, tone mapping, and content decisions still matter.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Good “First Questions” For XR-4 Work}
\p{Ask up to 3 (only if needed):}

\ol{
\li{Are we targeting OpenXR (recommended) or SteamVR/OpenVR legacy content?}
\li{Which tracking variant do you have: inside-out only or XR-4 base station tracking?}
\li{What’s the priority: max fidelity (PPD) or stable frame time (comfort)?}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Interleave With}
\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb steamvr-tracking\stopverb} for base station specs/placement and pairing}
\li{\code{\startverb xr-color-management\stopverb} for wide-gamut pipeline and debugging}
}
}
}